<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<em>It appears like the Phial of Galadriel at first - but wait! It is a cursed phial created by an evil wizard to lure adventurers into wielding it unknowingly.</em> <p>
The Phial of Undeath is as rare as the <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Spoilers_2fArtifacts_2fPhial_20of_20Galadriel"><img src="./wiki/classic/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">Phial of Galadriel</a>. If you find a <a class="nonexistent" href="./phial">phial</a>, make sure to <a class="nonexistent" href="./identify">identify</a> so you don't end up with undeadly lighting your way up. The Phial of Undeath is a <a class="nonexistent" href="./cursed">cursed</a> <a href="./Artifact">Artifact</a> and it will greatly disappoint you if you find it before the <em>real</em> <a class="nonexistent" href="./phial">phial</a>. 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 It provides light (<strong>radius 5</strong>) forever! It decreases all stats &amp; luck with 5.  
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 It allows you to <a href="./breathe_20without_20air">breathe without air</a>. It gives you <a class="nonexistent" href="./Undead">Undead</a> <a class="nonexistent" href="./ESP">ESP</a>. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 It is <a class="nonexistent" href="./cursed">cursed</a>. It carries an <strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./ancient_20morgothian_20curse">ancient morgothian curse</a></strong>! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 It can be activated for <a class="nonexistent" href="./ruination">ruination</a> every 10+d10 turns if it is being worn. 
</p>
</li>
</ul>

